 THEORY n. Used in the general sense of idea, plan, story, or set of rules.
This is a generalization and abuse of the technical meaning. "What's the
theory on fixing this TECO loss?" "What's the theory on dinner tonight?"
("Chinatown, I guess.") "What's the current theory on letting lusers on
during the day?" "The theory behind this change is to fix the following
well-known screw..."